n its invalidation check, so a `dimensionsOverride` can never silently reuse a wrong-dimension adapter. The bootstrap auto-selector now moves an explicit `EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER` to the front of the local-first cascade. The retention sweep re-validates `delete_after` inside the delete transaction, closing a multi-process data-loss window.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/feedback-safety-posture.vitest.ts:\n  Line 55:       delete_after TEXT\n\n  Line 61:       fsrs_stability, fsrs_difficulty, delete_after\n\n  Line 69:     SELECT importance_weight, importance_tier, state, fsrs_stability, fsrs_difficulty, delete_after\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/post-insert-metadata.ts:\n  Line 49:   delete_after?: string | null;\n\n  Line 66:   'governed_at', 'retention_policy', 'delete_after', 'governance_metadata',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/governance-e2e.vitest.ts:\n  Line 29:       delete_after TEXT\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/reconsolidation.ts:\n  Line 1086:     delete_after: existingRow.delete_after,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/19--feature-flag-reference/soft-delete-tombstones.md:\n  Line 18: - Prompt: `Validate SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES with default hard-delete, enabled tombstone, and disabled rollback steps.`\n\n  Line 31: Validate SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES with default hard-delete, enabled tombstone, and disabled rollback steps.\n\n  Line 37: 2. Unset the flag: `unset SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n\n  Line 40: 5. Enable tombstones: `export SPECKIT_SOFT