uture acceptance-criteria traceability table rendering in scaffold templates | acceptance coverage gate |\n| Acceptance coverage gate | OFF | `SPECKIT_AC_COVERAGE` | Opt-in advisory scan for acceptance-criteria traceability coverage during spec validation | acceptance coverage gate |","lineStart":80,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":652,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","time":{"start":1781763567785,"end":1781763567791}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff3e867158b7514016a338defa4588191a912d8bebafe8877"}},"id":"prt_ed96270a8001TTRc80FgKxRFkV","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed9623d81001ZD4CnY9vwm6oiQ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763567794,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UcgDKdmc7tLePaV30K907lR2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/19--feature-flag-reference/soft-delete-tombstones.md","offset":35,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/19--feature-flag-reference/soft-delete-tombstones.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n35: \n36: 1. Create an isolated DB sandbox and record its path in the transcript.\n37: 2. Unset the flag: `unset SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n38: 3. Save a sandbox memory with `memory_save({ filePath: \"<absolute file A>\", force: true })`, capture `ID_A`, then delete it with `memory_delete({ id: ID_A, confirm: true })`.\n39: 4. Verify `memory_list({ limit: 100, includeArchived: true })` or direct sandbox DB inspection no longer returns `ID_A` as an active or tombstoned row.\n40: 5. Enable tombstones: `export SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES=true`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n41: 6. Save a second sandbox memory, capture `ID_B`, delete it, then inspect the sandbox DB row for `deleted_at` and active/tombstone partition state.\n42: 7. Delete `ID_B` again or rerun the delete path and verify `deleted_at` is not overwritten.\n43: 8. Run `memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: true })` or the retention preview path and capture tombstone purgeability counters if available.\n44: 9. Disable the flag, restart, save/delete `ID_C`, and verify the hard-delete behavior matches step 4.\n45: \n46: ### Expected\n47: \n48: - `ID_A` and `ID_C` are removed by hard-delete semantics.\n49: - `ID_B` remains only as a tombstoned row with a populated first `deleted_at` timestamp.\n50: - Repeated tombstone delete does not change the first `deleted_at` value.\n51: - Retention preview distinguishes purgeable tombstone rows from active rows.\n52: \n53: ### Evidence\n54: \n55: Sandbox DB path, three save/delete transcripts, `deleted_at` inspection for the enabled run, retention preview output, and final sandbox cleanup.\n56: \n57: ### Pass / Fail\n58: \n59: - **Pass**: tombstones are absent by default, present only when enabled, stable across repeated delete, and absent again after disabling.\n60: - **Fail**: default delete writes tombstones, enabled delete hard-deletes, repeated delete overwrites `deleted_at`, or recall surfaces return tombstoned rows without an explicit diagnostic query.\n61: \n62: ### Failure Triage\n63: \n64: Inspect schema v37 migration paths, delete handler branching, retention sweep partition logic, and `tests/causal-edge-tombstones.vitest.ts`. Confirm the sandbox DB is isolated before diagnosing recall behavior.\n\n(Showing lines 35-64 of 90. Use offset=65 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n1. Create an isolated DB sandbox and record its path in the transcript.\n2. Unset the flag: `unset SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n3. Save a sandbox memory with `memory_save({ filePath: \"<absolute file A>\", force: true })`, capture `ID_A`, then delete it with `memory_delete({ id: ID_A, confirm: true })`.\n4. Verify `memory_list({ limit: 100, includeArchived: true })` or direct sandbox DB inspection no longer returns `ID_A` as an active or tombstoned row.\n5. Enable tombstones: `export SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES=true`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n6. Save a second sandbox memory, capture `ID_B`, delete it, then inspect the sandbox DB row for `deleted_at` and active/tombstone partition state.\n7. Delete `ID_B` again or rerun the delete path and verify `deleted_at` is not overwritten.\n8. Run `memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: true })` or the retention preview path and capture tombstone purgeability counters if available.\n9. Disable the flag, restart, save/delete `ID_C`, and verify the hard-delete behavior matches step 4.\n\n### Expected\n\n- `ID_A` and `ID_C` are removed by hard-delete semantics.\n- `ID_B` remains only as a tombstoned row with a populated first `deleted_at` timestamp.\n- Repeated tombstone delete does not change the first `deleted_at` value.\n- Retention preview distinguishes purgeable tombstone rows from active rows.\n\n### Evidence\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/19--feature-flag-reference/soft-delete-tombstones.md","text":"\n1. Create an isolated DB sandbox and record its path in the transcript.\n2. Unset the flag: `unset SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n3. Save a sandbox memory with `memory_save({ filePath: \"<absolute file A>\", force: true })`, capture `ID_A`, then delete it with `memory_delete({ id: ID_A, confirm: true })`.\n4. Verify `memory_list({ limit: 100, includeArchived: true })` or direct sandbox DB inspection no longer returns `ID_A` as an active or tombstoned row.\n5. Enable tombstones: `export SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES=true`; restart the daemon or handler process.\n6. Save a second sandbox memory, capture `ID_B`, delete it, then inspect the sandbox DB row for `deleted_at` and active/tombstone partition state.\n7. Delete `ID_B` again or rerun the delete path and verify `deleted_at` is not overwritten.\n8. Run `memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: true })` or the retention preview path and capture tombstone purgeability counters if available.\n9. Disable the flag, restart, save/delete `ID_C`, and verify the hard-delete behavior matches step 4.\n\n### Expected\n\n- `ID_A` and `ID_C` are removed by hard-delete semantics.\n- `ID_B` remains only as a tombstoned row with a populated first `deleted_at` timestamp.\n- Repeated tombstone delete does not change the first `deleted_at` value.\n- Retention preview distinguishes purgeable tombstone rows from active rows.\n\n### Evidence\n\nSandbox DB path, three save/delete transcripts, `deleted_at` inspection for the enabled run, retention preview output, and final sandbox cleanup.\n\n### Pass / Fail\n\n- **Pass**: tombstones are absent by default, present only when enabled, stable across repeated delete, and absent again after disabling.\n- **Fail**: default delete writes tombstones, enabled delete hard-deletes, repeated delete overwrites `deleted_at`, or recall surfaces return tombstoned rows without an explicit diagnostic query.\n\n### Failure Triage\n\nInspect schema v37 migration paths, delete handler branching, retention sweep partition logic, and `tests/causal-edge-tombstones.vitest.ts`. Confirm the sandbox DB is isolated before diagnosing recall behavior.","lineStart":35,"lineEnd":64,"totalLines":90,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/19--feature-flag-reference/soft-delete-tombstones.md","time":{"start":1781763567789,"end":1781763567793}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff3e867158b7514016a338defa4608191a35f9972d455b415"}},"id":"prt_ed96270aa001p3jk1aLpXO5q2E","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed9623d81001ZD4CnY9vwm6oiQ"}}
