{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763589692,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_3lGHzIoPPVKL5ICj1KmALeQm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"cancelledScanEnvelope|status: 'cancelled'|scan was cancelled|coalesced","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","include":"*.{ts,md}"},"output":"Found 35 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:\n  Line 415: `memory_index_scan` is self-maintaining: overlapping scan calls return a `coalesced:true` success envelope instead of a raw E429 error. Rows become BM25/FTS-searchable immediately as `pending` while vectors drain (`complete_with_pending_vectors` with a `pendingVectors` count). Move reconciliation heals renamed spec folders by packet identity without re-embedding. Each scan also runs a bounded global orphan sweep. `memory_health` now includes an `index` block with a summary enum (`healthy_fresh`, `healthy_lagging_vectors`, `stale_needs_scan`, `degraded_needs_repair`, `unavailable`) and counts for indexed/pending/failed rows.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:\n  Line 731: - Overlapping scan calls return a `coalesced: true` success envelope (status `coalesced`) instead of an error.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md:\n  Line 172: | `handlers/memory-index.ts` | Implements `memory_index_scan`. Overlapping scan calls return a `coalesced:true` success envelope rather than an error. Rows are committed BM25/FTS5-searchable as pending while vectors drain async. Status is `complete_with_pending_vectors` with a `pendingVectors` count when deferred work remains. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/embedder-reindex.vitest.ts:\n  Line 219:     expect(cancelled).toMatchObject({ id: jobId, status: 'cancelled' });\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts:\n  Line 382: function cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey: string): MCPResponse {\n\n  Line 386:     data: { status: 'cancelled', cancelled: true, scanKey },\n\n  Line 387:     hints: ['The scan was cancelled via memory_index_scan_cancel'],\n\n  Line 452:       message = 'A scan is already in progress; this call coalesced onto it.';\n\n  Line 456:       message = 'A scan recently completed; this call coalesced onto the recent scan window.';\n\n  Line 459:       status: 'coalesced',\n\n  Line 468:         coalesced: true,\n\n  Line 469:         status: 'coalesced',\n\n  Line 531:     return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n\n  Line 1034:         return { status: 'cancelled' } as IndexResult;\n\n  Line 1203:           return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n\n  Line 1232:     return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n\n  Line 1321:               return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/stress_test/durability/index-scan-coalescing-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 68:     // bounded wait — a clean coalesced refusal, never a raw E429-class error.\n\n  Line 85:     // A second burst immediately after completion must be coalesced by the\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/handler-memory-index-scan-jobs.vitest.ts:\n  Line 374:     mocks.mockIndexMemoryFile.mockResolvedValue({ status: 'cancelled' });\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/file-watcher.vitest.ts:\n  Line 474:     // Should have coalesced to exactly 1 reindex call\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/observability/retrieval-observability.ts:\n  Line 61:   lastStatus: 'success' | 'error' | 'coalesced' | null;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts:\n  Line 195:   it('splits coalesced client frames and caches initialize by method', () => {\n\n  Line 503:   it('primes coalesced post-handshake frames into the backend splitter', async () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/handler-memory-index-cooldown.vitest.ts:\n  Line 220:     expect(envelope.data.coalesced).toBe(true);\n\n  Line 221:     expect(envelope.data.status).toBe('coalesced');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/graph-lifecycle.ts:\n  Line 350:  * Multiple calls within the debounce window are coalesced — only the last\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 463: Additional contract (026 self-maintaining behavior): `Run two overlapping memory_index_scan calls and confirm the second returns a success envelope with coalesced:true rather than a raw E429. Then run a scan after saving a document whose spec folder has been renamed and confirm the handler heals the move by packet identity without re-embedding the content. Capture evidence that a completed scan result can carry status complete_with_pending_vectors with a non-zero pendingVectors count when vectors are still draining. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with cited field names.`\n\n  Line 465: Overlapping scan returns coalesced:true success envelope instead of E429; renamed spec folder healed by packet identity without re-embedding; complete_with_pending_vectors status present with non-zero pendingVectors when vectors are still draining; BM25/FTS rows are searchable while vectors drain (lexical-first commit confirmed)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/08--bug-fixes-and-data-integrity/error-code-reference.md:\n  Line 30: | `E429` | Handler envelope (`RATE_LIMITED`) | Legacy / registered (not raised on the routine scan path) | **Legacy.** The `RATE_LIMITED: 'E429'` code is still registered, but the `memory_index_scan` lease/cooldown guard no longer rejects routine overlapping or too-soon scans with it. Instead, an overlapping or too-soon scan now coalesces onto the in-progress or recently completed scan and returns a `coalesced:true` SUCCESS envelope (`status: 'coalesced'`) carrying the `reason` (`lease_active` for an overlapping fresh scan, `cooldown` for too soon after a completed scan), `waitSeconds`, and `nextPollAfterMs`. | `lib/errors/core.ts` (`RATE_LIMITED: 'E429'`, registered); coalesced success returned by `handlers/memory-index.ts` via `lib/response/envelope.ts` |\n\n  Line 42: - **`E429`** (legacy): no longer raised on the routine scan path. A routine overlapping or too-soon scan returns a `coalesced:true` SUCCESS envelope instead — treat that success as \"your scan joined the active/recent one\"; if you need a fresh result, poll again after the returned `nextPollAfterMs`/`waitSeconds`. The lease/cooldown guard exists to prevent overlapping and crash-leftover scans.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:\n  Line 718: **Phase 013 self-maintaining additions (026):** Overlapping scan requests no longer surface a raw E429 error. The handler detects an active lease and returns a `coalesced: true` success envelope with the computed wait time, so callers can treat concurrent scans as success. Lexical-first async commit means a newly indexed row is BM25/FTS5-searchable immediately with `embedding_status: 'pending'` while its vector drains in the background. The response envelope reports `status: 'complete_with_pending_vectors'` alongside a `pendingVectors` count. Move reconciliation heals renamed spec folders by matching on packet identity (`specId` / folder slug) without re-embedding any content. A bounded global orphan sweep runs once per scan to remove stale `memory_index` rows whose source files are no longer present on disk.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:\n  Line 353: `memory_index_scan` is self-maintaining from spec 026 onward. Overlapping scan calls return a `coalesced: true` success envelope instead of a raw E429 error. Rows become BM25/FTS-searchable immediately as `pending` while vectors drain (`complete_with_pending_vectors` with a `pendingVectors` count), so content is always text-searchable even when the embedding queue is backed up. Move reconciliation heals renamed spec folders by packet identity without re-embedding. Each scan also runs a bounded global orphan sweep.\n\n  Line 401: | `E429` | Legacy | The former index rate-limit class. The self-maintaining `memory_index_scan` contract replaced it with a `coalesced: true` success envelope, so a routine overlapping scan no longer returns `E429`. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/memory_system.md:\n  Line 463: The `memory_index_scan` operation is self-maintaining. Overlapping scans coalesce into a successful `coalesced: true` envelope instead of failing with the old cooldown error, and rows become BM25/FTS-searchable while embeddings drain in the background.\n","metadata":{"matches":35,"truncated":false},"title":"cancelledScanEnvelope|status: 'cancelled'|scan was cancelled|coalesced","time":{"start":1781763589646