tion-manager.ts`, `lib/storage/checkpoints.ts`, `lib/storage/incremental-index.ts`, `lib/ops/job-store.ts`, `lib/ops/job-queue.ts`, `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`.\n- Checked docs/tests around retention/tombstones and scan lifecycle.\n- Determined `atomicIndexMemory` indexes before final rename is covered/expected by tests; not enough to report as defect.\n\n### In Progress\n- Verifying possible async ingest path-handling TOCTOU: `memory_ingest_start` canonicalizes at enqueue; worker may only `access()` before `indexMemoryFile`; need confirm whether `indexMemoryFile` revalidates realpath/allowed roots.\n- Need write deep-review packet/artifacts under the lineage dir.\n\n### Blocked\n- Code graph queries blocked: `code_graph_full_scan_required: git HEAD changed: 8b9ff540 -> 2b64f293; 442 stale files exceed selective threshold (50); inline full scan skipped for read path`.\n- Did not run `code_graph_scan` because it would mutate global index state outside lineage artifact dir.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- Proceeded despite memory trigger error because file-based lineage state is sufficient.\n- Use direct file reads/grep instead of code graph due stale graph and write-scope restriction.\n- Do not report atomic rename/index ordering unless a stronger shipped-behavior contradiction is found.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Finish checking `handlers/memory-save.ts` / `indexMemoryFile` path validation for async ingest TOCTOU.\n- Re-read exact line ranges for retention sweep candidate and scan lease candidate to capture `file:line` evidence.\n- Classify findings P0/P1/P2 or PASS.\n- Write `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `iterations/iteration-001.md`, and `review-report.md` under `/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-r