 isolated correctness findings landed with regression tests. The execution-router adapter cache now includes the resolved dimension in its invalidation check, so a `dimensionsOverride` can never silently reuse a wrong-dimension adapter. The bootstrap auto-selector now moves an explicit `EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER` to the front of the local-first cascade. The retention sweep re-validates `delete_after` inside the delete transaction, closing a multi-process data-loss window.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts:\n  Line 4: // Enforces governed memory_index.delete_after metadata.\n\n  Line 25: /** Options for a governed memory retention sweep. */\n\n  Line 43:  * Beyond `delete_after`, the row carries tier and usage metadata so the\n\n  Line 134:   return process.env.SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES?.trim().toLowerCase() === 'true';\n\n  Line 143:   const usePurgeableIndex = useSoftDeleteTombstones && hasDeletedAt && hasIndex(database, 'idx_memory_purgeable_retention');\n\n  Line 145:     ? 'memory_index INDEXED BY idx_memory_purgeable_retention'\n\n  Line 148:   const tombstonePredicate = useSoftDeleteTombstones && hasDeletedAt ? 'AND deleted_at IS NOT NULL' : '';\n\n  Line 165:       delete_after AS deleteAfter,\n\n  Line 169:     WHERE delete_after IS NOT NULL\n\n  Line 171:       AND datetime(delete_after) < datetime('now')\n\n  Line 172:     ORDER BY datetime(delete_after) ASC, id ASC\n\n  Line 196: // clear delete_after between candidate selection and deletion, so a row that is\n\n  Line 208:   const tombstonePredicate = useSoftDeleteTombstones && presentColumns.has('deleted_at') ? 'AND deleted_at IS NOT NULL' : '';\n\n  Line 224:       delete_after AS deleteAfter,\n\n  Line 229:       AND delete_after IS NOT NULL\n\n  Line 231:       AND datetime(delete_after) < datetime('now')\n\n  Line 262:     usingPurgeableIndex: usesPurgeablePartition && hasIndex(da