run or a background job.\n\n  Line 1528:           && (scanData as { cancelled?: unknown }).cancelled === true);\n\n  Line 1532:           await completeJob(jobId, { state: 'cancelled', result: scanData });\n\n  Line 1548:         // Covers every terminal exit (complete / cancelled / failed / thrown).\n\n  Line 1557:     tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n\n  Line 1561:       'Use memory_index_scan_status with jobId to poll progress',\n\n  Line 1562:       'Use memory_index_scan_cancel with jobId to stop the scan',\n\n  Line 1582: const handle_memory_index_scan = handleMemoryIndexScan;\n\n  Line 1591:   handle_memory_index_scan,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/05--lifecycle/async-ingestion-job-lifecycle-p0-3.md:\n  Line 18: - Real user request: `Please validate Async ingestion job lifecycle (P0-3) against memory_ingest_start({paths:[\"specs/<target-spec>/decision-record.md\",\"specs/<target-spec>/decision-record.md\",\"specs/<target-spec>/implementation-summary.md\"]}) and tell me whether the expected signals are present: Job state transitions through queued→parsing→embedding→indexing→complete in order; duplicate input paths are deduplicated before queueing with explicit reporting; cancel sets state to cancelled; job IDs match nanoid format; incomplete jobs re-enqueue after restart.`\n\n  Line 21: - Expected signals: Job state transitions through queued→parsing→embedding→indexing→complete in order; duplicate input paths are deduplicated before queueing with explicit reporting; cancel sets state to cancelled; job IDs match nanoid format; incomplete jobs re-enqueue after restart\n\n  Line 39: 3. start a new job, then `memory_ingest_cancel({ jobId:\"<job-id>\" })` → verify cancelled state\n\n  Line 45: Job state transitions through queued→parsing→embedding→indexing→complete in order; duplicate input paths are deduplicated before queueing with explicit reporting; cancel sets state to cancelled; job IDs match nanoid format; incomplete jobs re-enqueue after restart\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/types.ts:\n  Line 66:   tool?: 'memory_save' | 'memory_index_scan' | 'refreshGraphMetadata' | 'reindexSpecDocs' | 'runEnrichmentBackfill';\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-stats.ts:\n  Line 54:       error: 'Database not initialized. Run memory_index_scan() to trigger schema creation, or restart the MCP server.',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-embedding-reconcile.ts:\n  Line 31:         hint: 'Restart the MCP server or run memory_index_scan() to reinitialize the database.',\n\n  Line 32:         actions: ['Restart the MCP server', 'Call memory_index_scan()'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.0.0.1.md:\n  Line 51: 3. Run `memory_index_scan({ force: true })` to re-index all spec documents and rebuild causal chains.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.0.1.3.md:\n  Line 28: The system prevents index scans from running too frequently using a cooldown timer. But the check was a classic \"time-of-check vs time-of-use\" race: read the last scan time, check if enough time has passed, then update the timestamp. Two requests arriving in the same millisecond could both pass the check and both start scanning, wasting resources and potentially conflicting. The cooldown is now an atomic lease. A single database transaction checks the timer and reserves the scan slot in one step -- if the lease is fresh, the request is rejected immediately. The lease includes a crash-expiry timer, so if a scan process dies mid-way, the slot is automatically freed after 2 minutes instead of being permanently locked.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/job-queue-state-edge.vitest.ts:\n  Line 219:     const cancelled = await mod.cancelIngestJob(job.id);\n\n  Line 220:     expect(cancelled.id).toBe(job.id);\n\n  Line 221:     expect(cancelled.state).toBe('complete');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts:\n  Line 2874:         provenanceSource: governance?.normalized.provenanceSource || (indexingOrigin === 'scan' ? 'memory_index_scan' : undefined),\n\n  Line 2876:         tool: indexingOrigin === 'scan' ? 'memory_index_scan' : 'memory_save',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.2.0.md:\n  Line 87: The spec-memory MCP had been failing every write with `SQLITE_CONSTRAINT_PRIMARYKEY` since the session began, blocking `memory_save`, `memory_index_scan`, and `memory_match_triggers`.\n\n  Line 91: A clean daemon restart cleared it. `memory_health` reports HEALTHY with FTS integrity ok and zero constraint errors, and the repair was verified the right way this time, through real MCP writes: `memory_index_scan` succeeded across the session's new packets with zero errors. The diagnostic-only `/doctor memory` references in the packet docs were corrected to point at the guarded `memory_health` autoRepair path, and the three packet docs that had drifted into mutual contradiction were reconciled to the verified outcome.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index-alias.ts:\n  Line 10: // Feature catalog: Workspace scanning and indexing (memory_index_scan)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts:\n  Line 61:       hint: 'Restart the MCP server or run memory_index_scan() to reinitialize the database',\n\n  Line 62:       actions: ['Restart the MCP server', 'Call memory_index_scan()'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/05--lifecycle/checkpoint-v2-needs-rebuild-self-heal.md:\n  Line 12: The sentinel is repaired at two entry points: at daemon boot, and during a `memory_index_scan` after the scan lease is acquired. The user-observable value is that an operator who restores a snapshot does not have to manually trigger every derived rebuild — the next boot or scan converges the index and clears the sentinel.\n\n  Line 22: - Prompt: `Validate the .needs-rebuild self-heal: confirm the sentinel is repaired at daemon boot and during a memory_index_scan after the scan lease is acquired, and that a successful repair clears the sentinel. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with cited field names.`\n\n  Line 66: As a lifecycle validation operator, validate the scan-lease .needs-rebuild repair against memory_index_scan with a sentinel present. Verify the scan acquires its lease, runs the sentinel repair, and surfaces the repair counts (completed, failed, skipped, cleared) in the response. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.\n\n  Line 71: 1. With a sandbox DB that has a `.needs-rebuild` sentinel, run memory_index_scan(force:false).\n\n  Line 77: The scan reserves `scan_started_at` via `acquireIndexScanLease`, then runs `runCheckpointNeedsRebuildRepairForScan` (source `memory_index_scan`); the response carries the repair counts and `cleared:true` on success.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/05--lifecycle/checkpoint-restore-checkpoint-restore.md:\n  Line 69: 3. Session B: memory_index_scan(specFolder)\n\n  Line 83: - **Pass**: `memory_save`, `memory_index_scan`, and `memory_bulk_delete` each return `E_RESTORE_IN_PROGRESS` before the restore exits\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"memory_index_scan|scan cancel|cancelled|coalesced|cooldown|last_index_scan|recently completed","time":{"start":1781763801430,"end":1781763801469}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c18aed70562d181016a338ed94a3c81919f3b1e5576907b9d"}},"id":"prt_ed9660153001elS3YKYpzq704W","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed965cd6e001RxAh7i7SgfJURD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763801472,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_zR2EI2WRNhnOBRJJYcG2xk4r","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: All paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n8: - `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n9: - `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n10: - `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n11: - semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n12: \n13: ## Review dimensions\n14: correctness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n15: \n16: ## Notes\n17: This round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n18: \n19: ## If MCP tools hang or error\n20: The `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back — use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit — direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error\nThe `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back — use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit — direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error\nThe `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back — use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit — direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":20,"totalLines":20,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","time":{"start":1781763801445,"end":1781763801471}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c18aed70562d181016a338ed94a44819199fd0a4f45c92b27"}},"id":"prt_ed9660163001yX2QqovHiI