{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763826935,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dnSo6GE2598Aabqc8yYBX9f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n14: \n15: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n22: \n23: ### Usage\n24: \n25: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n26: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n27: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n28: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n29: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. TOPIC\n34: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n40: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n41: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n42: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n43: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n44: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n49: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n54: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n59: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n60: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n61: \n62: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n63: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n64: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n65: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n70: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n71: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n72: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n73: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n74: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n75: \n76: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n77: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n82: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n83: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n88: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n89: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n94: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n95: \n96: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n97: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n98: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n99: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n100: \n101: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n102: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n103: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n108: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n109: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n114: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n115: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n121: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n126: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n127: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n128: \n129: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n130: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n131: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n132: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n133: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n134: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n135: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n136: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n137: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n142: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n143: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n144: \n145: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n146: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n147: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n148: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n153: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n154: - Max iterations: [from config]\n155: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n156: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n157: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n158: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n159: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n160: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n161: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n162: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n163: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n164: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n165: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n166: - Started: [timestamp]\n167: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n172: \n173: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n174: \n175: ```markdown\n176: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n177: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n178: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n179: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n180: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n181: \n182: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n183: - Dimension: test-coverage\n184: - Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n185: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n186: \n187: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n188: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n189: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n190: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n191: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n192: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n193: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n194: ```\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781763826930,"end":1781763826934}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e716757cd99cad4016a338ef2bdb8819185878383d729af52"}},"id":"prt_ed96664e4001BxCt4p34fIRvku","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed966283a001kmljRcszCbUCrx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763826954,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tK5MyIxONmyP56vXS7u5NkXI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review dashboard\"\n6:   - \"review session overview\"\n7:   - \"review findings summary\"\n8:   - \"review coverage trend\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: general\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n14: \n15: Auto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n22: 1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n23: 2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n24: 3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n29: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n30: - **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n31: - **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. STATUS\n36: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n37: - Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n38: - Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n39: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n40: - Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n41: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n42: - Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n43: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n44: - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n45: - hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n51: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n52: - **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n53: - **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n54: - **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n55: - **Repeated findings:** [N]\n56: - **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n57: - **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n58: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. PROGRESS\n63: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n64: \n65: | # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n66: |---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n67: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n68: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 5. COVERAGE\n73: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n74: - Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n75: - Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n76: - Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n77: - Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 6. TREND\n83: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n84: - Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n85: - New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n86: - Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n87: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n92: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n93: - **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n94: - **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n95: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n100: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n101: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n102: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n107: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n108: - [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n114: \n115: Reference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n116: \n117: ```markdown\n118: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n119: \n120: ## 2. STATUS\n121: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n122: - Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n123: - Status: ITERATING\n124: - Iteration: 4 of 7\n125: - Verdict: PENDING\n126: - Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n127: \n128: ## 3. PROGRESS\n129: \n130: | # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n131: |---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n132: | 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n133: | 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n134: | 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n135: | 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n136: \n137: ## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n138: - Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n139: - Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n140: - Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n141: \n142: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n143: - 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n144: - agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n145: ```\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n- Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n- hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **Repeated findings:** [N]\n- **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n- **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. PROGRESS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n| # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n- Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n- Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 6. TREND\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n- New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n- **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n- Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 4 of 7\n- Verdict: PENDING\n- Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n|---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n| 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n| 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n| 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n| 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n\n## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n- Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n- Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n- Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n- 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n- agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781763826936,"end":1781763826953}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e716757cd99cad4016a338ef2bdc48191a120250e4b6e5865"}},"id":"prt_ed96664f3001QNouD6r97pKZ3l","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed966283a001kmljRcszCbUCrx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763826955,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YjjU6S1Xrq9wxEAXQNcbQ6sC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\"\n3: description: \"Verify that review-report.md contains all 9 required sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\n7: \n8: This document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors, and metadata for `DRV-025`.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: This scenario validates review report synthesis has all 9 sections for `DRV-025`. The objective is to verify that the final `review-report.md` produced during synthesis contains all 9 required sections with their expected content.\n15: \n16: ### WHY THIS MATTERS\n17: \n18: The review report is the primary deliverable of the entire deep review loop. If any section is missing, the report cannot serve its purpose as a complete audit record, remediation guide, and planning input. The 9-section structure ensures that findings, evidence, verdicts, and next steps are all captured in a single canonical document.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n23: \n24: Operators should run this as a real orchestrator-led check rather than a synthetic command-matrix exercise. The scenario is only complete when the operator can explain the behavior back to a user in plain language.\n25: \n26: - Objective: Verify review-report.md has all 9 sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix.\n27: - Real user request: When the review finishes, what exactly does it produce and what sections does the report contain?\n28: - Prompt: `Validate deep-review report synthesis and confirm review-report.md contains all 9 required sections.`\n29: - Expected execution process: Inspect the quick reference review-report sections table, then the YAML synthesis step, then the SKILL.md and README for report section documentation.\n30: - Desired user-facing outcome: The user is told exactly what the review report contains and can verify completeness by checking for all 9 section headers.\n31: - Expected signals: All 9 section headers present, Executive Summary contains verdict and P0/P1/P2 counts, Active Finding Registry has deduplicated findings with evidence, and Audit Appendix includes convergence data.\n32: - Pass/fail posture: PASS if all 9 sections are documented and enforced by the synthesis step. FAIL if any section is missing from the template or synthesis contract.\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n37: \n38: ### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n39: \n40: 1. Restate the user request in plain language before inspecting implementation details.\n41: 2. Follow the listed command sequence in order so higher-level docs are checked before lower-level workflow contracts.\n42: 3. Capture evidence that would let another operator reproduce the verdict without re-deriving the scenario.\n43: 4. Return a short user-facing explanation, not just raw implementation notes.\n44: ### Prompt\n45: Validate deep-review report synthesis and confirm review-report.md contains all 9 required sections.\n46: ### Commands\n47: 1. `bash: rg -n 'Executive Summary|Planning Trigger|Active Finding Registry|Remediation Workstreams|Spec Seed|Plan Seed|Traceability Status|Deferred Items|Audit Appendix|review-report' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`\n48: 2. `bash: rg -n 'review-report|synthesis|9.*section|Executive Summary|Planning Trigger|Active Finding|Remediation|Spec Seed|Plan Seed|Traceability|Deferred|Audit Appendix' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml`\n49: 3. `bash: rg -n 'review-report|synthesis|9.*section|report.*section|Executive Summary|verdict|hasAdvisories' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md .opencode/commands/deep/review.md`\n50: ### Expected\n51: All 9 section headers present, Executive Summary contains verdict and P0/P1/P2 counts, Active Finding Registry has deduplicated findings, Audit Appendix includes convergence data.\n52: ### Evidence\n53: Capture the 9-section table from quick reference, the YAML synthesis step, and the report structure documentation from SKILL.md.\n54: ### Pass/Fail\n55: PASS if all 9 sections are documented and enforced by the synthesis step. FAIL if any section is missing from the template or synthesis contract.\n56: ### Failure Triage\n57: Privilege the quick reference section table as the canonical list and verify the YAML synthesis step produces all 9 sections.\n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n61: \n62: ### PLAYBOOK SOURCES\n63: \n64: | File | Role |\n65: |---|---|\n66: | `manual_testing_playbook.md` | Root directory page, integrated review protocol, and scenario summary |\n67: | `feature_catalog/` | No dedicated feature catalog exists yet for `deep-review`, use the live docs below as the implementation contract |\n68: \n69: ### IMPLEMENTATION AND RUNTIME ANCHORS\n70: \n71: | File | Role |\n72: |---|---|\n73: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | Canonical 9-section table, use `ANCHOR:review-report-sections` |\n74: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Synthesis step producing review-report.md |\n75: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Synthesis step producing review-report.md |\n76: | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` | Command entrypoint, output format documentation |\n77: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md` | Review report structure and verdict rules, use `ANCHOR:how-it-works` |\n78: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md` | Feature summary for review report synthesis |\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n83: \n84: - Group: SYNTHESIS, SAVE, AND GUARDRAILS\n85: - Playbook ID: DRV-025\n86: - Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook.md`\n87: - Feature file path: `06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md`\n88: - Feature catalog status: No `feature_catalog/` package exists under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/` as of 2026-03-28.\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\"\ndescription: \"Verify that review-report.md contains all 9 required sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix.\"\n---\n\n# DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\n\nThis document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors, and metadata for `DRV-025`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario validates review report synthesis has all 9 sections for `DRV-025`. The objective is to verify that the final `review-report.md` produced during synthesis contains all 9 required sections with their expected content.\n\n### WHY THIS MATTERS\n\nThe review report is the primary deliverable of the entire deep review loop. If any section is missing, the report cannot serve its purpose as a complete audit record, remediation guide, and planning input. The 9-section structure ensures that findings, evidence, verdicts, and next steps are all captured in a single canonical document.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\"\ndescription: \"Verify that review-report.md contains all 9 required sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix.\"\n---\n\n# DRV-025 -- Review report synthesis has all 9 sections\n\nThis document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors, and metadata for `DRV-025`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario validates review report synthesis has all 9 sections for `DRV-025`. The objective is to verify that the final `review-report.md` produced during synthesis contains all 9 required sections with their expected content.\n\n### WHY THIS MATTERS\n\nThe review report is the primary deliverable of the entire deep review loop. If any section is missing, the report cannot serve its purpose as a complete audit record, remediation guide, and planning input. The 9-section structure ensures that findings, evidence, verdicts, and next steps are all captured in a single canonical document.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\nOperators should run this as a real orchestrator-led check rather than a synthetic command-matrix exercise. The scenario is only complete when the operator can explain the behavior back to a user in plain language.\n\n- Objective: Verify review-report.md has all 9 sections: Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix.\n- Real user request: When the review finishes, what exactly does it produce and what sections does the report contain?\n- Prompt: `Validate deep-review report synthesis and confirm review-report.md contains all 9 required sections.`\n- Expected execution process: Inspect the quick reference review-report sections table, then the YAML synthesis step, then the SKILL.md and README for report section documentation.\n- Desired user-facing outcome: The user is told exactly what the review report contains and can verify completeness by checking for all 9 section headers.\n- Expected signals: All 9 section headers present, Executive Summary contains verdict and P0/P1/P2 counts, Active Finding Registry has deduplicated findings with evidence, and Audit Appendix includes convergence data.\n- Pass/fail posture: PASS if all 9 sections are documented and enforced by the synthesis step. FAIL if any section is missing from the template or synthesis contract.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n\n1. Restate the user request in plain language before inspecting implementation details.\n2. Follow the listed command sequence in order so higher-level docs are checked before lower-level workflow contracts.\n3. Capture evidence that would let another operator reproduce the verdict without re-deriving the scenario.\n4. Return a short user-facing explanation, not just raw implementation notes.\n### Prompt\nValidate deep-review report synthesis and confirm review-report.md contains all 9 required sections.\n### Commands\n1. `bash: rg -n 'Executive Summary|Planning Trigger|Active Finding Registry|Remediation Workstreams|Spec Seed|Plan Seed|Traceability Status|Deferred Items|Audit Appendix|review-report' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`\n2. `bash: rg -n 'review-report|synthesis|9.*section|Executive Summary|Planning Trigger|Active Finding|Remediation|Spec Seed|Plan Seed|Traceability|Deferred|Audit Appendix' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml`\n3. `bash: rg -n 'review-report|synthesis|9.*section|report.*section|Executive Summary|verdict|hasAdvisories' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md .opencode/commands/deep/review.md`\n### Expected\nAll 9 section headers present, Executive Summary contains verdict and P0/P1/P2 counts, Active Finding Registry has deduplicated findings, Audit Appendix includes convergence data.\n### Evidence\nCapture the 9-section table from quick reference, the YAML synthesis step, and the report structure documentation from SKILL.md.\n### Pass/Fail\nPASS if all 9 sections are documented and enforced by the synthesis step. FAIL if any section is missing from the template or synthesis contract.\n### Failure Triage\nPrivilege the quick reference section table as the canonical list and verify the YAML synthesis step produces all 9 sections.\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE FILES\n\n### PLAYBOOK SOURCES\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `manual_testing_playbook.md` | Root directory page, integrated review protocol, and scenario summary |\n| `feature_catalog/` | No dedicated feature catalog exists yet for `deep-review`, use the live docs below as the implementation contract |\n\n### IMPLEMENTATION AND RUNTIME ANCHORS\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | Canonical 9-section table, use `ANCHOR:review-report-sections` |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Synthesis step producing review-report.md |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Synthesis step producing review-report.md |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` | Command entrypoint, output format documentation |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md` | Review report structure and verdict rules, use `ANCHOR:how-it-works` |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md` | Feature summary for review report synthesis |\n\n---\n\n## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: SYNTHESIS, SAVE, AND GUARDRAILS\n- Playbook ID: DRV-025\n- Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook.md`\n- Feature file path: `06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md`\n- Feature catalog status: No `feature_catalog/` package exists under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/` as of 2026-03-28.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":88,"totalLines":88,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/review-report-synthesis-has-all-9-sections.md","time":{"start":1781763826946,"end":1781763826954}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e716757cd99cad4016a338ef2bdcc8191abddbb558122e870"}},"id":"prt_ed96664f8001u7N6tKfFUsc82S","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed966283a001kmljRcszCbUCrx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763826982,"sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Syx0YCFiq6SrpavG0cOBlaYz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\"\n3: description: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out review config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge with p0/p1/p2 binding → step_derive_verdict using merged counts → review-report.md.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # DRV-064 -- Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\n7: \n8: This document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DRV-064`.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: End-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the review loop, with particular\n15: attention to the review-specific `bind_from_output` that feeds merged P0/P1/P2 counts to\n16: `step_derive_verdict`.\n17: \n18: ### Why This Matters\n19: \n20: The review fan-out has one critical additional requirement beyond the research fan-out: the\n21: `bind_from_output` binding in `step_fanout_merge`. Without it, `step_derive_verdict` reads\n22: zero counts from the empty base artifact dir state log and produces an incorrect PASS verdict.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n27: \n28: - Objective: Confirm the review YAML dispatches CLI lineages, that `step_fanout_merge` has `bind_from_output` for P0/P1/P2 counts, and that `step_derive_verdict` would use merged counts.\n29: - Real user request: `/deep:review:auto \"skill:deep-research\" --executor=cli-codex --model=o4-mini --label=codex --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude --concurrency=2`\n30: - Expected execution process: 1. Setup binds two executors → `config.fanout`. 2. `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs --loop-type review`. 3. Pool spawns two subprocesses. 4. `step_fanout_merge` calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type review` and binds `active_p0/p1/p2` → `p0_count/p1_count/p2_count`. 5. `step_derive_verdict` derives verdict from bound counts.\n31: - Expected signals: `step_fanout_merge` YAML block has `bind_from_output: {p0_count: \"active_p0\", ...}`; `fanout-merge.vitest.ts` review tests pass (5 tests).\n32: - Pass/fail: PASS if `bind_from_output` present and review tests pass; FAIL if binding absent.\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n37: \n38: ### Prerequisites\n39: \n40: - Working directory is repository root.\n41: - `deep_review_auto.yaml` and `review.md` present.\n42: \n43: ### Steps\n44: \n45: 1. `bash: grep -n \"step_fanout_spawn\\|step_fanout_merge\\|bind_from_output\\|active_p0\\|active_p1\\|skip_when\" .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml | head -25`\n46: 2. Confirm `step_fanout_merge` has `bind_from_output:` mapping `active_p0` → `p0_count`, `active_p1` → `p1_count`, `active_p2` → `p2_count`.\n47: 3. Confirm `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs` with `--loop-type review`.\n48: 4. `bash: grep -n \"fanout_executors\\|--executor\\|strongest.restriction\\|merged FAIL\" .opencode/commands/deep/review.md | head -15`\n49: 5. Confirm strongest-restriction note in review command docs.\n50: 6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts --reporter=verbose`\n51: 7. Confirm 10/10 pass (5 review tests + 3 research tests + 2 e2e tests).\n52: \n53: ### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n54: \n55: 1. Check `bind_from_output` in the YAML first — this is the review-specific requirement.\n56: 2. Verify the loop type in the CLI call (`--loop-type review`).\n57: 3. Confirm the review command docs include the strongest-restriction note.\n58: 4. Run fanout-merge tests last as regression confirmation.\n59: \n60: ### Expected Outcome\n61: \n62: Source inspection confirms `bind_from_output` mapping is present. Review command docs include strongest-restriction. fanout-merge.vitest.ts 10/10 pass.\n63: \n64: ### Failure Modes\n65: \n66: - `bind_from_output` absent: `step_derive_verdict` reads zero counts → incorrect PASS even when lineages found P0.\n67: - `--loop-type research` used instead of `review` in CLI call: merge uses research dedup instead of strongest-restriction.\n68: - Review strongest-restriction note absent from docs: operators don't know P0 in any lineage blocks.\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n73: \n74: ### Implementation\n75: \n76: | File | Role |\n77: |---|---|\n78: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge` (with `bind_from_output`), `step_resolve_artifact_root` |\n79: | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` | `--executor` flag docs, strongest-restriction note |\n80: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Review strongest-restriction merge |\n81: \n82: ### Validation\n83: \n84: | File | Role |\n85: |---|---|\n86: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | 10 tests including 5 review strongest-restriction |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n91: \n92: - Group: Fan-Out\n93: - Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`\n94: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md`\n95: - Expected verdict mode: GREEN when bind_from_output confirmed + 10/10 fanout-merge tests pass\n96: - Wall-time estimate: 10-20 min\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\"\ndescription: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out review config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge with p0/p1/p2 binding → step_derive_verdict using merged counts → review-report.md.\"\n---\n\n# DRV-064 -- Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DRV-064`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nEnd-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the review loop, with particular\nattention to the review-specific `bind_from_output` that feeds merged P0/P1/P2 counts to\n`step_derive_verdict`.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThe review fan-out has one critical additional requirement beyond the research fan-out: the","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\"\ndescription: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out review config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge with p0/p1/p2 binding → step_derive_verdict using merged counts → review-report.md.\"\n---\n\n# DRV-064 -- Fan-out review with two CLI lineages\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DRV-064`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nEnd-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the review loop, with particular\nattention to the review-specific `bind_from_output` that feeds merged P0/P1/P2 counts to\n`step_derive_verdict`.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThe review fan-out has one critical additional requirement beyond the research fan-out: the\n`bind_from_output` binding in `step_fanout_merge`. Without it, `step_derive_verdict` reads\nzero counts from the empty base artifact dir state log and produces an incorrect PASS verdict.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Objective: Confirm the review YAML dispatches CLI lineages, that `step_fanout_merge` has `bind_from_output` for P0/P1/P2 counts, and that `step_derive_verdict` would use merged counts.\n- Real user request: `/deep:review:auto \"skill:deep-research\" --executor=cli-codex --model=o4-mini --label=codex --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude --concurrency=2`\n- Expected execution process: 1. Setup binds two executors → `config.fanout`. 2. `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs --loop-type review`. 3. Pool spawns two subprocesses. 4. `step_fanout_merge` calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type review` and binds `active_p0/p1/p2` → `p0_count/p1_count/p2_count`. 5. `step_derive_verdict` derives verdict from bound counts.\n- Expected signals: `step_fanout_merge` YAML block has `bind_from_output: {p0_count: \"active_p0\", ...}`; `fanout-merge.vitest.ts` review tests pass (5 tests).\n- Pass/fail: PASS if `bind_from_output` present and review tests pass; FAIL if binding absent.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Working directory is repository root.\n- `deep_review_auto.yaml` and `review.md` present.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. `bash: grep -n \"step_fanout_spawn\\|step_fanout_merge\\|bind_from_output\\|active_p0\\|active_p1\\|skip_when\" .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml | head -25`\n2. Confirm `step_fanout_merge` has `bind_from_output:` mapping `active_p0` → `p0_count`, `active_p1` → `p1_count`, `active_p2` → `p2_count`.\n3. Confirm `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs` with `--loop-type review`.\n4. `bash: grep -n \"fanout_executors\\|--executor\\|strongest.restriction\\|merged FAIL\" .opencode/commands/deep/review.md | head -15`\n5. Confirm strongest-restriction note in review command docs.\n6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts --reporter=verbose`\n7. Confirm 10/10 pass (5 review tests + 3 research tests + 2 e2e tests).\n\n### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n\n1. Check `bind_from_output` in the YAML first — this is the review-specific requirement.\n2. Verify the loop type in the CLI call (`--loop-type review`).\n3. Confirm the review command docs include the strongest-restriction note.\n4. Run fanout-merge tests last as regression confirmation.\n\n### Expected Outcome\n\nSource inspection confirms `bind_from_output` mapping is present. Review command docs include strongest-restriction. fanout-merge.vitest.ts 10/10 pass.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- `bind_from_output` absent: `step_derive_verdict` reads zero counts → incorrect PASS even when lineages found P0.\n- `--loop-type research` used instead of `review` in CLI call: merge uses research dedup instead of strongest-restriction.\n- Review strongest-restriction note absent from docs: operators don't know P0 in any lineage blocks.\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge` (with `bind_from_output`), `step_resolve_artifact_root` |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` | `--executor` flag docs, strongest-restriction note |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Review strongest-restriction merge |\n\n### Validation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | 10 tests including 5 review strongest-restriction |\n\n---\n\n## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n\n- Group: Fan-Out\n- Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`\n- Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md`\n- Expected verdict mode: GREEN when bind_from_output confirmed + 10/10 fanout-merge tests pass\n- Wall-time estimate: 10-20 min","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":96,"totalLines":96,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-review.md","time":{"start":1781763826978,"end":1781763826981}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e716757cd99cad4016a338ef2bdd48191a7d2642c933e568c"}},"id":"prt_ed9666514001cN2Met4hhCa6f6","sessionID":"ses_126a03146ffe6yn9ha3tk3Qb0n","messageID":"msg_ed966283a001kmljRcszCbUCrx"}}
